The ability to communicate directly with a foreigner automatically puts a person with language skills ahead of the competition.
According to a 2013 YouGov survey, 75% of over 4,000 British adults are unable to have a conversation in a foreign language, and French was the only language known to a double-digit figure of 15%.
This is why investing in language teaching is important for today’s children.
In particular, knowledge of the languages of developing countries gives children a better chance of finding a meaningful career.
Within Scotland, schools differ in what languages they teach.
Several schools focus on traditional languages, while some specifically teach languages that are supposedly important to British people in 2020, such as Mandarin Chinese and Japanese.
Despite the interests of your child, private schools always have several language options taught by specialized teachers.
Scottish private schools are dedicated to providing a learning environment that prepares children and equips them with the skills needed to succeed, whatever the future holds.
