Tomorrow, individual performances are the top priority, and then we will talk about different things.
It’s great to be on the field with a partner when everything is going well, but when you’re on the field alone, the player’s capacity is tested to the bottom.
This is a message that needs to be passed on to the players - tomorrow everyone will be able to deliver the best performance.
Now you have to give up a partner who can go to the field alone and do his best.”
Unlike Bjorn, opposing captain Jim Furyk will require his players to perform better as individuals than they could as partners, with the exception of Jordan Spieth and Justin Thomas, who collected three points out of four.
